The paper proposes a new nonlinear factorization model for graphs, which is a machine learning topic and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model is designed for clustering graphs, which is a task related to data structures and algorithms, and thus, it can also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The model uses a pseudometric called Gromov-Wasserstein discrepancy, which is a mathematical concept and can be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the model can be applied to graphs with node attributes, which can be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves image processing and analysis.
